 it seems the test didn't initialize the closure class properly. While `Class.forName` does seem to work, the method in question may not be calling correctly, or maybe it just invokes without the expected results. I wonder if I should add an assertion for the negative path? Also, I'll check the old test results after the external test — perhaps our test didn't run as expected? The `build/test-results/test` directory could be where I find useful information.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_U7exLfZrZIfQOOXvdbzj9x1I|fc_0a9dd3da3ffcca8d016a0050b09d7081918af8c64041f095c4", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find tests/src/io.rest-assured/json-path/5.5.0/build/test-results/test -name 'TEST-*.xml' -maxdepth 1 -print | sort | xargs -r grep -H \"testsuite\" | head -20"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 841, "output": 1683, "cacheRead": 30208, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 32732, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778405525390, "responseId": "resp_0a9dd3da3ffcca8d016a005095ecfc8191aa914f874c615150"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_U7exLfZrZIfQOOXvdbzj9x1I|fc_0a9dd3da3ffcca8d016a0050b09d7081918af8c64041f095c4", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "tests/src/io.rest-assured/json-path/5.5.0/build/test-results/test/TEST-io_rest_assured.json_path.ConfigurableJsonSlurperInnerClinitClosure1Test.xml:<testsuite name=\"io_rest_assured.json_path.ConfigurableJsonSlurperInnerClinitClosure1Test\" tests=\"1\" skipped=\"0\" failures=\"0\" errors=\"0\" timestamp=\"2026-05-10T09:31:13.830Z\" hostname=\"kung-fu-workstation\" time=\"0.198\">\ntests/src/io.rest-assured/json-path/5.5.0/build/test-results/test/TEST-io_rest_assured.json_path.ConfigurableJsonSlurperInnerClinitClosure1Test.xml:</testsuite>\ntests/src/io.rest-assured/json-path/5.5.0/build/test-results/test/TEST-io_rest_assured.json_